This is where a home data center transforms from a lab into a literal enterprise operations simulator. In the corporate world, Sysadmins live and breathe **Identity Management (Active Directory)** and **Unified Endpoint Management (MDM)**.

Using your actual spare inventory—the old MacBook, the Dell laptops, and a pile of old phones—gives you a concrete, tangible hardware fleet to enforce real-world policies on.

Below is a production-level deployment blueprint for your repository. It walks you through setting up a Microsoft Active Directory domain controller on your Proxmox server, configuring an open-source cross-platform device manager (**FleetDM**), and registering your actual physical devices into the system.

